      "body" : "Understood, and this is how XML2JSON works as well.  However, most parsers will assume that phonenumbers is an array, not an object.  Wouldn&#39;t your solution not make phonenumbers an array when it only contains a single phonenumber element?  Most consumers of the JSON won&#39;t always check whether it&#39;s an array or object, and assume it to be an array, causing problems for cases when there&#39;s only one &#39;phonenumber&#39; in &#39;phonenumbers&#39;."
